ICMP 

- Type: 0 
- Code: 0

- Datagram
- Response Time

-Network Testing

-Uses Datagrams (IP stack)

- Core in IP suite

- ping command

	- widely used to test the connections between computers


- tracert command
	
	- uses ping, repeatedly, with increasing ICMP Time To Live, to reach progressively farther through the routers


- Supports a series of of network testing and error messages

- Carries NO Payload

- Not used in Application layer, Tecnically Network layer



- Uses Two general types of messages

	-> Error messages
	-> Informal messages

- Used for connectivity testing

- Types for Error Messages

	- 0-127 cover error messages
	- 128-255 cover informational messages
 

